President Obama called Governor Jerry Brown to discuss the recent wildfires in California. The President expressed concern about the impact of the wildfires on the state and its citizens, and thanked the firefighters and emergency responders for their efforts. He assured Governor Brown that the federal government will continue to support the state and local efforts. The President also emphasized the need to fix the way the nation pays for wildfire suppression and reduce the risk of future wildfires. He reiterated his commitment to working closely with Governor Brown in preparing California for the effects of climate change. The President expressed his thoughts and prayers for the people of California during this difficult time.